This paper discusses the optimization of DNN accelerators, which involves computer vision (CV), artificial intelligence (AI), and machine learning (ML) techniques. The paper also discusses the use of Halide compiler, which is a tool for image processing and computer vision applications, indicating that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.AR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of resource allocation and blocking, which are related to system design and control, indicating that the paper could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), Long Short-Term Memories (LSTMs), and multi-layer perceptrons (MLPs), indicating that the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
